properties.desc: This route goes through Helen McDowell Sanctuary on the east side of Seward Highway.  Not the most direct route, but very pleasant.
From the Chester Creek Trail via Denali St.
Another east-sde route from Elmore. This uses a nice trail through UAA, and riding on the north side of 36th is pretty decent.

This route takes the Campbell Creek trail from the east, past old RDI, then up Fairbanks and Eagle streets.  From there, you can continue straight up Denali, but I like to swing through Cuddy Park.  A minute or two longer, but nicer.
East-side route via the Chester Creek Trail
Loop around APU.  The shortcut through UAA is faster, but this is nicer.
This route is for visitors staying at the Crowne Plaza. No frills, utilitarian.
